Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

fixes dual interface tethering on mata

Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

> Patch Set 1: Verified-1
> 
> branch

pig: pls to fix

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1: -Code-Review
> 
> > Patch Set 1: Verified-1
> > 
> > branch
> 
> pig: pls to fix

https://review.lineageos.org/c/LineageOS/android_hardware_interfaces/+/296611 the other guy cherry-picked before I moved other changes 😐

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

> Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1
> 
> fixes dual interface tethering on mata

Dual interface tethering works fine on xiaomi msm8998 and cheryl without this chain of commits. You are probably missing commits device side.

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1
> 
> > Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1
> > 
> > fixes dual interface tethering on mata
> 
> Dual interface tethering works fine on xiaomi msm8998 and cheryl without this chain of commits. You are probably missing commits device side.

mata’s kernel is very old, based on LA.UM.6 from what I can see. Both Xiaomi MSM8998 and cheryl are based on newer CAF kernels. I can confirm dual interface tethering works with a rebased kernel on mata

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1
> 
> > Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+1
> > 
> > fixes dual interface tethering on mata
> 
> Dual interface tethering works fine on xiaomi msm8998 and cheryl without this chain of commits. You are probably missing commits device side.

Same on every device I have, but I don't see why we couldn't merge the full chain given that one commit is already needed for wifi/tethering actually work.

Patch Set 1:

> Same on every device I have, but I don't see why we couldn't merge the full chain given that one commit is already needed for wifi/tethering actually work.

Because it's better to fix the actual issue instead of blind picking commits. This chain adds support for qcom features that don't work without extensive changes in other repositories as well.
